lead_paragraph: A WEST COUNTRY VILLAGE, England. A DOLF HITLER has wrought a great and surprising change in this village between the rugged cliffs of the Western Sea -- a village that once helped to man Drake's ships, whose inhabitants have lived unruffled, have even profited, by centuries of wars.
abstract: effect of war on Brit West Country village described
